h intensify rapidly, but dissipate just as fast if not faster.\n\n- Anonymous\n|\nI don’t want just words. If that’s all you have for me, you’d better go\n\n- F. Scott Fitzgerald, The Beautiful and Damned\n|\nYour mind is like a tunnel that has no end, and a baloon, that even too much air cannot burst.\n\n- Michael\n|\nCelebrate my heart, at ease or on fire, in my usual featherbrained way.Horace, Roman PoetOde I-6, 23 BCE\n\n- Vivian Swift, When Wanderers Cease to Roam: A Traveler's Journal of Staying Put\n|\nI will not go back. I may stumble, but I will not fall.\n\n- Aimee L. Salter, Dark Touch\n|\nLoveless work, boring work, work valued only because others haven't got even that much, however loveless and boring--this is one of the harshest human miseries.\n\n- Wisława\n|\nNow I understand why women want to have children - it's simply the urge to create happiness for yourself, somehow to fill the oppressive, unbearable emptiness in your soul.\n\n- Nina Lugovskaya, I Want To Live: The Diary of a Young Girl in Stalin's Russia\n|\nThey did it quite a lot after that first encounter' ... when Jill remembers first meeting the dashing Baron.\n\n- Lisa\n|\nLife is a bonfire where everyone else has brought marshmallows, and you—a stick.\n\n- Richelle E. Goodrich, Making Wishes\n|\nThe question should be who do we want to be when we grow up, not what.\n\n- Craig  Stone, The Squirrel that Dreamt of Madness\n|\nThough we think we see different things from our windows, in reality we see the same things: Happiness and sorrow! All that is seen from every window!\n\n- Mehmet\n|\nAs regards moral courage, then, it is not so much that the public schools support it feebly, as that they suppress it firmly.\n\n- G.K.\n|\nWeeping is not the same thing as crying. It takes your whole body to weep, and when it's over, you feel like you don't have any bones left to hold you up.\n\n- Sarah Ockler, Twenty Boy Summer\n|\nThis place is alive,' Sunni said in wonder. 'Things are moving. Inside a